for storing boardstate/pieces, consider:
  instead of storing the fen each move, store a list of pieces the player still has
  The parser would still simulate the game each move to track pieces, the db would just store
  what pieces are left for each player each move, and this way we could also store the captured piece
  
  So we would end up storing a string, like if a player had all their pieces 
  "ppppppppNNBBRRKQ"

  This is almost a fen, but instead of position it's just a list of pieces. So if 2 pawns and a rook get captured,
  "ppppppNNBBRKQ"

  I'd have to look into how you could query this, to see if you can make LIKE "%R%" work in some way that accounts for if the player had two rooks

  Zig provides a fmt function (can't remember what its called) to format strings like print does, which would make this easy

  Could also consider just numbering it instead (like huffman encoding) "8P2N2B2R1K1Q" which would make the code part easy, not so sure about the query

